). Forewing about three times longer than tall. Costal area: greatest height ̴0.17 times height of wing; tallest at costal cell (#4–5). Subcosta: two crossveins below stigma. Ten radial crossveins (between R and Rs); two rows of gradates; inner row with four gradates, outer row with six, both rows in regular, parallel pattern. Cubitus: icux2 curved, thickened, with small, bubble-like expansion mesally.

Abdomen (male & female) (Table 5; Figs 6 , 11). Cream-colored, dorsally with faint, broken, brown mesal stripe, mottled brown spotting sublaterally; pleural regions creamcolored, without marks; sternites cream-colored, except S5, 6 (male) dark brown, S5 (female) dark brown; setae (female) cream-colored basally, brown distally;
setae (male) long, cream-colored throughout. Tergites 6, 7: length: 2.3–3.0 ( T6 ), 1.8–2.1 ( T7 ) times greater than height (lateral view). Sternite 6: length ̴0.9–1.0 times height. Spiracles ̴ 0.05–0.06 mm diameter
; atria noticably larger than spiracular openings.
